  "root_text": {
    "iti34:0.1": "Itivuttaka 34 ",
    "iti34:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti34:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti34:0.4": "Ātāpīsutta ",
    "iti34:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti34:2.1": "“Anātāpī, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anottāpī abhabbo sambodhāya, abhabbo nibbānāya, abhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya. ",
    "iti34:2.2": "Ātāpī ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ottāpī bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo nibbānāya, bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāyā”ti. ",
    "iti34:2.3": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti34:2.4": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti34:3.1": "“Anātāpī anottāpī, ",
    "iti34:3.2": "kusīto hīnavīriyo; ",
    "iti34:3.3": "Yo thinamiddhabahulo, ",
    "iti34:3.4": "ahirīko anādaro; ",
    "iti34:3.5": "Abhabbo tādiso bhikkhu, ",
    "iti34:3.6": "phuṭṭhuṁ sambodhimuttamaṁ. ",
    "iti34:4.1": "Yo ca satimā nipako jhāyī, ",
    "iti34:4.2": "Ātāpī ottāpī ca appamatto; ",
    "iti34:4.3": "Saṁyojanaṁ jātijarāya chetvā, ",
    "iti34:4.4": "Idheva sambodhimanuttaraṁ phuse”ti. ",
    "iti34:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti34:5.2": "Sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti34:0.1": "So It Was Said 34 ",
    "iti34:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti34:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti34:0.4": "Keen ",
    "iti34:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti34:2.1": "“Mendicants, without being keen and prudent a mendicant can’t achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary from the yoke. ",
    "iti34:2.2": "But if a mendicant is keen and prudent they can achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary from the yoke.” ",
    "iti34:2.3": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti34:2.4": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti34:3.1": "“Neither keen nor prudent, ",
    "iti34:3.2": "lazy, lacking energy, ",
    "iti34:3.3": "full of dullness and drowsiness, ",
    "iti34:3.4": "unconscientious, lacking regard for others, ",
    "iti34:3.5": "such a mendicant is incapable ",
    "iti34:3.6": "of experiencing the highest awakening. ",
    "iti34:4.1": "One who is mindful, alert, meditative, ",
    "iti34:4.2": "keen, prudent, and diligent, ",
    "iti34:4.3": "having cut the fetter of birth and old age, ",
    "iti34:4.4": "would experience supreme awakening <j>in this very life.” ",
    "iti34:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti34:2.1": "anottāpī → anottappī (si, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti34:2.2": "ottāpī → ottappī (si, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti34:3.4": "ahirīko → ahiriko (sya-all) "
